    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="2023-11-26-2023-11-27"><a href="#2023-11-26-2023-11-27" class="headerlink" title="2023 .11.26 -2023 .11.27"></a>2023 .11.26 -2023 .11.27</h1><hr><h2 id="course-study"><a href="#course-study" class="headerlink" title="course study"></a>course study</h2><ol><li>English-language periodicals studying</li><li>Linear algebra studying and homework</li><li>Calculus studying and homework</li></ol><h2 id="achievement-criteria"><a href="#achievement-criteria" class="headerlink" title="achievement criteria"></a>achievement criteria</h2><h4 id="1-English-language-periodicals-studying"><a href="#1-English-language-periodicals-studying" class="headerlink" title="(1) English-language periodicals studying"></a>(1) English-language periodicals studying</h4><p>1.highlight and record unfamiliar words and sentence<br>2.outline the structure of the article<br>3.able to listen to it once without seeing the text</p><h4 id="2-Linear-algebra-studying-and-homework"><a href="#2-Linear-algebra-studying-and-homework" class="headerlink" title="(2) Linear algebra studying and homework"></a>(2) Linear algebra studying and homework</h4><p>1.finish homework<br>2.grasp the concept<br>3.grasp the essence of the question type<br>4.read the PPT of teacher</p><h4 id="3-Calculus-studying-and-homework"><a href="#3-Calculus-studying-and-homework" class="headerlink" title="(3) Calculus studying and homework"></a>(3) Calculus studying and homework</h4><p>2.grasp the concept<br>3.grasp the essence of the question type<br>4.read the PPT of teacher  </p><hr><h2 id="professional-study"><a href="#professional-study" class="headerlink" title="professional study"></a>professional study</h2><ol><li>Learn C++</li><li>study data structures and algorithms</li><li>using C++ to implement algorithms</li><li>study how to use hexo</li></ol><h2 id="achievement-criteria-1"><a href="#achievement-criteria-1" class="headerlink" title="achievement criteria"></a>achievement criteria</h2><h4 id="1-Learn-C"><a href="#1-Learn-C" class="headerlink" title="(1) Learn C++"></a>(1) Learn C++</h4><p>1.read C++ Primer Plus frome p80 to p165<br>2.take notes<br>3.do homework from C++ Primer Plus</p><h4 id="2-Study-data-structures-and-algorithms"><a href="#2-Study-data-structures-and-algorithms" class="headerlink" title="(2) Study data structures and algorithms"></a>(2) Study data structures and algorithms</h4><p>1.review linklist and learn linear list<br>2.take notes  </p><h4 id="3-Using-C-to-implement-algorithms"><a href="#3-Using-C-to-implement-algorithms" class="headerlink" title="(3) Using C++ to implement algorithms"></a>(3) Using C++ to implement algorithms</h4><p>1.implement linked list operations<br>2.implement linear list operations  </p><h4 id="4-Study-how-to-use-hexo"><a href="#4-Study-how-to-use-hexo" class="headerlink" title="(4) Study how to use hexo"></a>(4) Study how to use hexo</h4><p>1.learn how to make a radio button</p><hr><h2 id="literary-study"><a href="#literary-study" class="headerlink" title="literary study"></a>literary study</h2><ol><li>translate kill a Mockingbird</li><li>calligraphy practice</li></ol><h2 id="achievement-criteria-2"><a href="#achievement-criteria-2" class="headerlink" title="achievement criteria"></a>achievement criteria</h2><h4 id="1-Translate-kill-a-Mockingbird"><a href="#1-Translate-kill-a-Mockingbird" class="headerlink" title="(1) Translate kill a Mockingbird"></a>(1) Translate kill a Mockingbird</h4><p>1.translate 6 pages<br>2.take notes </p><h4 id="2-Calligraphy-practice"><a href="#2-Calligraphy-practice" class="headerlink" title="(2) Calligraphy practice"></a>(2) Calligraphy practice</h4><ol><li>practice 30 min</li></ol>]]></content>
    
    
    
