    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="2023-11-6"><a href="#2023-11-6" class="headerlink" title="2023.11.6"></a>2023.11.6</h1><hr><h2 id="C-Primer-Plus-Chapter-4"><a href="#C-Primer-Plus-Chapter-4" class="headerlink" title="C++ Primer Plus Chapter 4:"></a>C++ Primer Plus Chapter 4:</h2><h3 id="1-line-oriented-input"><a href="#1-line-oriented-input" class="headerlink" title="(1) line-oriented input:"></a>(1) line-oriented input:</h3><p> “cin” input stream is used for word-oriented input where it reads data encounters whitespace characters.<br>So we need a function for word-oriented input :<br><strong>1. cin.getline()</strong><br>cin.getline() reads a whole line ,it use the newline character entered by pressing the Enter key to determine the end of input.</p><figure class="highlight c++"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs C++">cin.<span class="hljs-built_in">getline</span>(name,n_length) <br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>EG:  </p><figure class="highlight c++"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs C++">cin.<span class="hljs-built_in">getline</span>(array_name,array_length);<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Notes:<br>1.The number of characters stored in “name” is one less than “n_length”<br>2.The </p><p>**2. cin.gets</p>]]></content>
    
    
    
